      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Those who claim that government ownership is wholly\nbad should read about the cement mill the government\nhas built in connection with the Salt river irrigation pro-\n5ect When the government asked for bids on cement the\nlowest offer So per barrel Later when the govern\nmen talked about making its cement the bids fell\nto $49S per barrel The government went ahead with the\nmill anyway and is actually turning out perfectly good\ncement at the rate of $192 per barrel\n\n\nFolks who think that all government work should be\ndone by private contract should put this item in their\npipe and smoke it,"
    }
